Note: ===================================================================
Note: HIR TO SOLIDITY CODE GENERATOR
Note: ===================================================================
Note: Generates Solidity smart contract code from High-level Intermediate Representation (HIR).
Note: Supports Solidity 0.8+ syntax including contracts, interfaces, libraries, events, modifiers.

Note: Part of the Translation Translation System
Note: Location: compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/backends/solidity/hir_to_solidity.runa
Note: ===================================================================

Note:
HIR CONSUMER MODEL (model 1, typed hir_nodes.runa surface)
==========================================================
This backend consumes the exact HIR shape the solidity_to_hir frontend produces.
All dispatch goes through hir_node_type(node) returning an HIR_* kind constant,
compared in an If-ladder (there is no hir_is_* predicate family). Accessors use
the real word order (hir_get_binary_left, not hir_binary_get_left). The module
exposes ONE declarations list (hir_get_declarations) holding classes (contracts/
interfaces/libraries/structs/errors) and enums intermixed, plus an imports list
(hir_get_imports); a class exposes ONE member list (hir_get_class_members) holding
fields, functions, and nested classes/enums intermixed. Each member is dispatched
by its node kind and, for classes/functions, its "solidity_type" metadata tag.

Operator precedence (Solidity, low -> high), used to decide parenthesisation in
generate_binary_expression so re-emitted source re-parses to the same tree:
  1 ternary  ?:
  2 ||
  3 &&
  4 == !=
  5 < <= > >=
  6 |          (bitwise or)
  7 ^          (bitwise xor)
  8 &          (bitwise and)
  9 << >>      (shifts)
 10 + -
 11 * / %
 12 **         (exponent)
A binary operand is wrapped in parentheses when its own operator binds LESS
tightly than the parent operator, preserving evaluation order across the round
trip. The exact Solidity operator spelling comes from "solidity_operator"
metadata (the HIR opcode alone cannot distinguish ** from *, or & from &&).
:End Note

Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore
Import "compiler/internal/string_utils.runa" as StringUtils
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa" as ListCore
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/hir_nodes.runa" as HIR

Note: ===================================================================
Note: GENERATION CONTEXT
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Per-translation context for Solidity emission. output accumulates the
generated source; indent_level controls per-line spacing;
current_contract is a back-pointer to the enclosing HIR class node so
member generation can consult contract-level metadata without
re-locating the contract.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Runa struct of three fields: output (running source string), indent_level
(Integer), current_contract (Integer handle to enclosing contract HIR node
or 0 at file scope). Constructed via create_generation_context with
empty/zero values; current_contract is set/cleared on entry/exit of
generate_contract.
@End Implementation
Type called "GenerationContext":
    output as Integer
    indent_level as Integer
    current_contract as Integer
End Type

Note: ===================================================================
Note: MAIN GENERATION ENTRY POINT
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Top-level driver. Creates a fresh GenerationContext and dispatches to
generate_module which emits the SPDX comment, pragma, imports,
file-scope declarations, and contracts. Returns the accumulated output.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Calls create_generation_context, then generate_module(ctx, hir_module),
then returns ctx.output.
@End Implementation
Process called "generate_solidity_from_hir" takes hir_module as Integer returns Integer:
    Let ctx be proc create_generation_context

    proc generate_module with ctx, hir_module

    Return ctx.output
End Process

@Reasoning:
Factory for GenerationContext. Initialises output to empty string,
indent_level to 0, and current_contract to 0 (file-scope marker).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Constructs a GenerationContext value with output="", indent_level=0,
current_contract=0. Returns the new value.
@End Implementation
Process called "create_generation_context" returns Integer:
    Let ctx be a value of type GenerationContext with
        output as "",
        indent_level as 0,
        current_contract as 0

    Return ctx
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: MODULE GENERATION
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Emits the full module preamble (SPDX license, pragma directive) then
walks the imports list and the single declarations list. Solidity files
must lead with an SPDX comment and pragma; if the HIR module supplies
pragma metadata it is used verbatim, otherwise a default
'pragma solidity ^0.8.0;' is emitted. The declarations list intermixes
contracts/interfaces/libraries (HIR_CLASS) with file-scope structs/
errors (also HIR_CLASS, distinguished by "solidity_type") and enums
(HIR_ENUM); each is dispatched by node kind and metadata tag.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Emits the SPDX comment and pragma. Iterates hir_get_imports calling
generate_import. Iterates hir_get_declarations: HIR_ENUM ->
generate_enum; HIR_CLASS routes on "solidity_type" ("struct" ->
generate_struct, "error" -> generate_error, otherwise generate_contract).
Blank lines separate declarations.
@End Implementation
Process called "generate_module" takes ctx as Integer, hir_module as Integer:
    proc emit with ctx, "// SPDX-License-Identifier: MIT\n"

    Let pragma_type be proc hir_get_metadata from HIR with hir_module, "solidity_pragma_type"
    Let pragma_value be proc hir_get_metadata from HIR with hir_module, "solidity_pragma_value"

    Let pragma_type_len be proc safe_string_length with pragma_type
    If pragma_type_len is greater than 0:
        proc emit with ctx, "pragma "
        proc emit with ctx, pragma_type
        Let pragma_value_len be proc safe_string_length with pragma_value
        If pragma_value_len is greater than 0:
            proc emit with ctx, " "
            proc emit with ctx, pragma_value
        End If
        proc emit with ctx, ";\n\n"
    Otherwise:
        proc emit with ctx, "pragma solidity ^0.8.0;\n\n"
    End If

    Note: Imports
    Let imports be proc hir_get_imports from HIR with hir_module
    Let import_count be 0
    If imports is not equal to 0:
        Set import_count to proc list_length from ListCore with imports
    End If
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than import_count:
        Let import_node be proc list_get from ListCore with imports, i
        proc generate_import with ctx, import_node
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    If import_count is greater than 0:
        proc emit with ctx, "\n"
    End If

    Note: Top-level declarations (contracts, interfaces, libraries, file-scope structs/enums/errors)
    Let declarations be proc hir_get_declarations from HIR with hir_module
    Let decl_count be 0
    If declarations is not equal to 0:
        Set decl_count to proc list_length from ListCore with declarations
    End If
    Set i to 0
    While i is less than decl_count:
        Let decl be proc list_get from ListCore with declarations, i
        proc generate_declaration with ctx, decl
        proc emit with ctx, "\n"
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
End Process

@Reasoning:
A top-level declaration is either a HIR_ENUM (file-scope enum) or a
HIR_CLASS whose "solidity_type" tag selects struct / error / contract
(contract covers contract/interface/library, further refined inside
generate_contract).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads hir_node_type. HIR_ENUM -> generate_enum. HIR_CLASS -> read
"solidity_type": "struct" -> generate_struct; "error" -> generate_error;
anything else -> generate_contract.
@End Implementation
Process called "generate_declaration" takes ctx as Integer, decl as Integer:
    Let kind be proc hir_node_type from HIR with decl

    If kind is equal to HIR.HIR_ENUM:
        proc generate_enum with ctx, decl
        Return
    End If

    If kind is equal to HIR.HIR_CLASS:
        Let solidity_type be proc hir_get_metadata from HIR with decl, "solidity_type"
        Let is_struct be proc safe_string_equals with solidity_type, "struct"
        Let is_error be proc safe_string_equals with solidity_type, "error"

        If is_struct is equal to 1:
            proc generate_struct with ctx, decl
            Return
        End If
        If is_error is equal to 1:
            proc generate_error with ctx, decl
            Return
        End If

        proc generate_contract with ctx, decl
        Return
    End If
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: IMPORT GENERATION
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Emits 'import "path";' or 'import "path" as Alias;'. Solidity's import
target is always quoted (a path or URI); the alias clause is optional
and recorded in "solidity_alias" metadata.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads the import path via hir_get_import_path. Emits 'import "PATH"'.
Reads 'solidity_alias' metadata; if non-empty emits ' as ALIAS'.
Terminates with ';\n'.
@End Implementation
Process called "generate_import" takes ctx as Integer, import_node as Integer:
    Let import_path be proc hir_get_import_path from HIR with import_node

    proc emit with ctx, "import \""
    proc emit with ctx, import_path
    proc emit with ctx, "\""

    Let alias be proc hir_get_metadata from HIR with import_node, "solidity_alias"
    Let alias_len be proc safe_string_length with alias
    If alias_len is greater than 0:
        proc emit with ctx, " as "
        proc emit with ctx, alias
    End If

    proc emit with ctx, ";\n"
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: TYPE GENERATION (STRUCTS, ENUMS, ERRORS)
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Emits 'struct Name { type1 field1; type2 field2; ... }' for a Solidity
value-type aggregate. Each field is emitted with its Solidity type
(from 'solidity_field_type' metadata) followed by the field name.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads struct name via hir_get_class_name. Emits 'struct NAME {\n'.
increase_indent. Iterates hir_get_class_members filtering HIR_FIELD:
each field becomes '<indent>TYPE NAME;\n'. decrease_indent. Emits '}\n'.
@End Implementation
Process called "generate_struct" takes ctx as Integer, struct_node as Integer:
    Let struct_name be proc hir_get_class_name from HIR with struct_node

    proc emit with ctx, "struct "
    proc emit with ctx, struct_name
    proc emit with ctx, " {\n"

    proc increase_indent with ctx

    Let members be proc hir_get_class_members from HIR with struct_node
    Let member_count be 0
    If members is not equal to 0:
        Set member_count to proc list_length from ListCore with members
    End If
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than member_count:
        Let member be proc list_get from ListCore with members, i
        Let member_kind be proc hir_node_type from HIR with member
        If member_kind is equal to HIR.HIR_FIELD:
            Let field_name be proc hir_get_field_name from HIR with member
            Let field_type be proc hir_get_metadata from HIR with member, "solidity_field_type"

            proc emit_indent with ctx
            proc emit_type with ctx, field_type
            proc emit with ctx, " "
            proc emit with ctx, field_name
            proc emit with ctx, ";\n"
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    proc decrease_indent with ctx
    proc emit_indent with ctx
    proc emit with ctx, "}\n"
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emits 'enum Name { V1, V2, ... }'. Variant names are stored in the
enum node's value list, read via hir_get_enum_values in declared order.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads enum name via hir_get_enum_name. Emits 'enum NAME {\n'.
increase_indent. Iterates hir_get_enum_values: each variant is emitted
on its own indented line with a trailing comma except the last.
decrease_indent + '}\n'.
@End Implementation
Process called "generate_enum" takes ctx as Integer, enum_node as Integer:
    Let enum_name be proc hir_get_enum_name from HIR with enum_node

    proc emit with ctx, "enum "
    proc emit with ctx, enum_name
    proc emit with ctx, " {\n"

    proc increase_indent with ctx

    Let values be proc hir_get_enum_values from HIR with enum_node
    Let value_count be 0
    If values is not equal to 0:
        Set value_count to proc list_length from ListCore with values
    End If
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than value_count:
        Let value be proc list_get from ListCore with values, i

        proc emit_indent with ctx
        proc emit with ctx, value

        If i is less than value_count minus 1:
            proc emit with ctx, ","
        End If

        proc emit with ctx, "\n"
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    proc decrease_indent with ctx
    proc emit_indent with ctx
    proc emit with ctx, "}\n"
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emits a Solidity 0.8.4+ custom error declaration:
'error Name(type1 field1, type2 field2);'. Error parameters are stored
as HIR fields whose Solidity type lives in 'solidity_field_type'.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads error name. Emits 'error NAME('. Iterates HIR_FIELD members:
each becomes 'TYPE NAME' separated by ', '. Terminates with ');\n'.
@End Implementation
Process called "generate_error" takes ctx as Integer, error_node as Integer:
    Let error_name be proc hir_get_class_name from HIR with error_node

    proc emit with ctx, "error "
    proc emit with ctx, error_name
    proc emit with ctx, "("

    Let members be proc hir_get_class_members from HIR with error_node
    Let member_count be 0
    If members is not equal to 0:
        Set member_count to proc list_length from ListCore with members
    End If
    Let emitted be 0
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than member_count:
        Let member be proc list_get from ListCore with members, i
        Let member_kind be proc hir_node_type from HIR with member
        If member_kind is equal to HIR.HIR_FIELD:
            If emitted is greater than 0:
                proc emit with ctx, ", "
            End If
            Let field_name be proc hir_get_field_name from HIR with member
            Let field_type be proc hir_get_metadata from HIR with member, "solidity_field_type"
            proc emit_type with ctx, field_type
            proc emit with ctx, " "
            proc emit with ctx, field_name
            Set emitted to emitted plus 1
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    proc emit with ctx, ");\n"
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: CONTRACT GENERATION
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Emits a Solidity contract, interface, or library with all members.
The 'solidity_type' metadata key selects the keyword ('contract' /
'interface' / 'library'); 'solidity_abstract' adds the 'abstract'
prefix. Inheritance is expressed via 'is Base1, Base2' from the
multi-valued 'solidity_inherits' metadata. The proc saves and restores
ctx.current_contract so member generators can consult enclosing-contract
metadata.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads contract name and 'solidity_type'/'solidity_abstract' metadata.
Emits 'abstract '? + keyword + name. Reads 'solidity_inherits' via
get_all_metadata_values; if non-empty emits ' is B1, B2, ...'. Emits
' {\n', increases indent, sets ctx.current_contract. Emits any
contract-scope using directive. Walks hir_get_class_members in source
order, dispatching each by node kind / "solidity_type" to the matching
member generator. Decreases indent, clears current_contract, '}\n'.
@End Implementation
Process called "generate_contract" takes ctx as GenerationContext, contract_node as Integer:
    Let contract_name be proc hir_get_class_name from HIR with contract_node

    Let solidity_type be proc hir_get_metadata from HIR with contract_node, "solidity_type"
    Let is_interface be proc safe_string_equals with solidity_type, "interface"
    Let is_library be proc safe_string_equals with solidity_type, "library"

    Let is_abstract be proc hir_get_metadata from HIR with contract_node, "solidity_abstract"
    Let abstract_len be proc safe_string_length with is_abstract
    If abstract_len is greater than 0:
        proc emit with ctx, "abstract "
    End If

    If is_interface is equal to 1:
        proc emit with ctx, "interface "
    Otherwise:
        If is_library is equal to 1:
            proc emit with ctx, "library "
        Otherwise:
            proc emit with ctx, "contract "
        End If
    End If

    proc emit with ctx, contract_name

    Let inherits_meta be proc hir_get_metadata from HIR with contract_node, "solidity_inherits"
    Let bases be proc get_all_metadata_values with inherits_meta
    Let base_count be proc list_length from ListCore with bases
    If base_count is greater than 0:
        proc emit with ctx, " is "
        Let b be 0
        While b is less than base_count:
            Let base_name be proc list_get from ListCore with bases, b
            proc emit with ctx, base_name
            If b is less than base_count minus 1:
                proc emit with ctx, ", "
            End If
            Set b to b plus 1
        End While
    End If

    proc emit with ctx, " {\n"

    proc increase_indent with ctx
    Set ctx.current_contract to contract_node

    proc generate_using_directive with ctx, contract_node

    Let members be proc hir_get_class_members from HIR with contract_node
    Let member_count be 0
    If members is not equal to 0:
        Set member_count to proc list_length from ListCore with members
    End If
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than member_count:
        Let member be proc list_get from ListCore with members, i
        proc generate_member with ctx, member

        If i is less than member_count minus 1:
            proc emit with ctx, "\n"
        End If

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    proc decrease_indent with ctx
    Set ctx.current_contract to 0

    proc emit with ctx, "}\n"
End Process

@Reasoning:
Dispatches a single contract member. Fields are state variables;
HIR_ENUM / nested HIR_CLASS members are nested enums/structs/errors;
HIR_FUNCTION members route on "solidity_type" to the event, modifier,
or function generator.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads hir_node_type. HIR_FIELD -> generate_state_variable. HIR_ENUM ->
generate_enum (indented). HIR_CLASS -> generate_struct / generate_error
(by "solidity_type"). HIR_FUNCTION -> event / modifier / function (by
"solidity_type").
@End Implementation
Process called "generate_member" takes ctx as Integer, member as Integer:
    Let kind be proc hir_node_type from HIR with member

    If kind is equal to HIR.HIR_FIELD:
        proc generate_state_variable with ctx, member
        Return
    End If

    If kind is equal to HIR.HIR_ENUM:
        proc emit_indent with ctx
        proc generate_enum with ctx, member
        Return
    End If

    If kind is equal to HIR.HIR_CLASS:
        Let nested_type be proc hir_get_metadata from HIR with member, "solidity_type"
        Let is_error be proc safe_string_equals with nested_type, "error"
        proc emit_indent with ctx
        If is_error is equal to 1:
            proc generate_error with ctx, member
        Otherwise:
            proc generate_struct with ctx, member
        End If
        Return
    End If

    If kind is equal to HIR.HIR_FUNCTION:
        Let func_type be proc hir_get_metadata from HIR with member, "solidity_type"
        Let is_event be proc safe_string_equals with func_type, "event"
        Let is_modifier be proc safe_string_equals with func_type, "modifier"

        If is_event is equal to 1:
            proc generate_event with ctx, member
            Return
        End If
        If is_modifier is equal to 1:
            proc generate_modifier with ctx, member
            Return
        End If
        proc generate_function with ctx, member
        Return
    End If
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emits 'using LIB for TYPE;' inside a contract when the contract carries
'solidity_using_library' metadata. A missing target type is emitted as
the global form 'using LIB for *'.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads 'solidity_using_library'; returns if absent. emit_indent + 'using
LIB for '; emits 'solidity_using_target' if present, else '*'; ';\n\n'.
@End Implementation
Process called "generate_using_directive" takes ctx as Integer, contract_node as Integer:
    Let library_name be proc hir_get_metadata from HIR with contract_node, "solidity_using_library"
    Let lib_len be proc safe_string_length with library_name
    If lib_len is equal to 0:
        Return
    End If

    proc emit_indent with ctx
    proc emit with ctx, "using "
    proc emit with ctx, library_name
    proc emit with ctx, " for "

    Let target_type be proc hir_get_metadata from HIR with contract_node, "solidity_using_target"
    Let target_len be proc safe_string_length with target_type
    If target_len is greater than 0:
        proc emit with ctx, target_type
    Otherwise:
        proc emit with ctx, "*"
    End If

    proc emit with ctx, ";\n\n"
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: STATE VARIABLE GENERATION
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Emits a contract state-variable declaration:
'TYPE [modifier...] NAME [= INIT];'. Solidity modifiers for state
variables include visibility (public/internal/private) and storage
classifiers (constant/immutable), collected from the multi-valued
'solidity_modifier' metadata in declared order.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
emit_indent. Emits 'TYPE ' from 'solidity_type' metadata. Emits each
'solidity_modifier' value followed by a space. Emits the field name.
If 'solidity_initializer' is non-null emits ' = INIT'. Terminates
';\n'.
@End Implementation
Process called "generate_state_variable" takes ctx as Integer, field_node as Integer:
    Let field_name be proc hir_get_field_name from HIR with field_node

    proc emit_indent with ctx

    Let field_type be proc hir_get_metadata from HIR with field_node, "solidity_type"
    proc emit_type with ctx, field_type
    proc emit with ctx, " "

    Let modifiers_meta be proc hir_get_metadata from HIR with field_node, "solidity_modifier"
    Let modifiers be proc get_all_metadata_values with modifiers_meta
    Let modifier_count be proc list_length from ListCore with modifiers
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than modifier_count:
        Let modifier be proc list_get from ListCore with modifiers, i
        proc emit with ctx, modifier
        proc emit with ctx, " "
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    proc emit with ctx, field_name

    Let initializer be proc hir_get_metadata from HIR with field_node, "solidity_initializer"
    If initializer is not equal to 0:
        proc emit with ctx, " = "
        proc generate_expression with ctx, initializer, 0
    End If

    proc emit with ctx, ";\n"
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: EVENT GENERATION
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Emits 'event Name(type1 indexed? name1, ...);'. Each parameter may
carry the 'indexed' modifier ('solidity_indexed'); the 'anonymous'
event-level modifier ('solidity_anonymous') is appended after ')'.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
emit_indent + 'event NAME('. Loops parameters; each yields 'TYPE
[indexed] [NAME]'. Parameters separated by ', '. After ')', emits '
anonymous' when 'solidity_anonymous' is non-empty. Terminates ';\n'.
@End Implementation
Process called "generate_event" takes ctx as Integer, event_node as Integer:
    Let event_name be proc hir_get_function_name from HIR with event_node

    proc emit_indent with ctx
    proc emit with ctx, "event "
    proc emit with ctx, event_name
    proc emit with ctx, "("

    Let params be proc get_parameter_list with event_node
    Let param_count be 0
    If params is not equal to 0:
        Set param_count to proc list_length from ListCore with params
    End If
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than param_count:
        Let param be proc list_get from ListCore with params, i
        Let param_name be proc hir_get_parameter_name from HIR with param
        Let param_type be proc hir_get_metadata from HIR with param, "solidity_type"

        proc emit_type with ctx, param_type

        Let is_indexed be proc hir_get_metadata from HIR with param, "solidity_indexed"
        Let indexed_len be proc safe_string_length with is_indexed
        If indexed_len is greater than 0:
            proc emit with ctx, " indexed"
        End If

        Let param_name_len be proc safe_string_length with param_name
        If param_name_len is greater than 0:
            proc emit with ctx, " "
            proc emit with ctx, param_name
        End If

        If i is less than param_count minus 1:
            proc emit with ctx, ", "
        End If

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    proc emit with ctx, ")"

    Let is_anonymous be proc hir_get_metadata from HIR with event_node, "solidity_anonymous"
    Let anon_len be proc safe_string_length with is_anonymous
    If anon_len is greater than 0:
        proc emit with ctx, " anonymous"
    End If

    proc emit with ctx, ";\n"
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: MODIFIER GENERATION
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Emits a Solidity modifier definition:
'modifier NAME(params) { body... }'. Modifiers are re-usable pre/post-
condition fragments composed onto functions. The '_;' placeholder
represents the wrapped function's body; when no body is provided this
generator emits a minimal '{ _; }' so the output is syntactically
valid.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
emit_indent + 'modifier NAME(' + comma-separated 'TYPE NAME' parameters
+ ')'. Calls generate_modifier_tail for any extra modifiers. If body is
non-null, delegates to generate_statement. Otherwise emits '{ _; }'.
@End Implementation
Process called "generate_modifier" takes ctx as Integer, modifier_node as Integer:
    Let modifier_name be proc hir_get_function_name from HIR with modifier_node

    proc emit_indent with ctx
    proc emit with ctx, "modifier "
    proc emit with ctx, modifier_name
    proc emit with ctx, "("

    Let params be proc get_parameter_list with modifier_node
    Let param_count be 0
    If params is not equal to 0:
        Set param_count to proc list_length from ListCore with params
    End If
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than param_count:
        Let param be proc list_get from ListCore with params, i
        proc generate_parameter with ctx, param
        If i is less than param_count minus 1:
            proc emit with ctx, ", "
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    proc emit with ctx, ") "

    Let body be proc hir_get_function_body from HIR with modifier_node
    If body is not equal to 0:
        proc generate_statement with ctx, body
    Otherwise:
        proc emit with ctx, "{\n"
        proc increase_indent with ctx
        proc emit_indent with ctx
        proc emit with ctx, "_;\n"
        proc decrease_indent with ctx
        proc emit_indent with ctx
        proc emit with ctx, "}\n"
    End If
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: FUNCTION GENERATION
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Emits a Solidity function declaration covering the four forms: regular
'function NAME', the unnamed 'constructor', 'fallback', and 'receive'.
Parameters carry an optional storage location (memory/calldata/storage)
between type and name. The returns clause uses the multi-valued
'solidity_return' metadata (each entry a "type[ name]" string).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
emit_indent. Reads 'solidity_type'. Branches:
  "constructor" -> 'constructor'
  "fallback"    -> 'fallback'
  "receive"     -> 'receive'
  else          -> 'function NAME'
Emits '('. Loops parameters via generate_parameter. Emits ')'. Calls
generate_modifier_tail (visibility/mutability/user modifiers). If any
'solidity_return' values exist, emits ' returns (V1, V2, ...)'. If body
is non-null emits ' ' + generate_statement; otherwise ';\n'.
@End Implementation
Process called "generate_function" takes ctx as Integer, function_node as Integer:
    Let function_name be proc hir_get_function_name from HIR with function_node
    Let solidity_type be proc hir_get_metadata from HIR with function_node, "solidity_type"

    proc emit_indent with ctx

    Let is_constructor be proc safe_string_equals with solidity_type, "constructor"
    Let is_fallback be proc safe_string_equals with solidity_type, "fallback"
    Let is_receive be proc safe_string_equals with solidity_type, "receive"

    If is_constructor is equal to 1:
        proc emit with ctx, "constructor"
    Otherwise:
        If is_fallback is equal to 1:
            proc emit with ctx, "fallback"
        Otherwise:
            If is_receive is equal to 1:
                proc emit with ctx, "receive"
            Otherwise:
                proc emit with ctx, "function "
                proc emit with ctx, function_name
            End If
        End If
    End If

    proc emit with ctx, "("

    Let params be proc get_parameter_list with function_node
    Let param_count be 0
    If params is not equal to 0:
        Set param_count to proc list_length from ListCore with params
    End If
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than param_count:
        Let param be proc list_get from ListCore with params, i
        proc generate_parameter with ctx, param
        If i is less than param_count minus 1:
            proc emit with ctx, ", "
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    proc emit with ctx, ")"

    proc generate_modifier_tail with ctx, function_node

    Let returns_meta be proc hir_get_metadata from HIR with function_node, "solidity_return"
    Let return_list be proc get_all_metadata_values with returns_meta
    Let return_count be proc list_length from ListCore with return_list
    If return_count is greater than 0:
        proc emit with ctx, " returns ("
        Let j be 0
        While j is less than return_count:
            Let return_slot be proc list_get from ListCore with return_list, j
            proc emit with ctx, return_slot
            If j is less than return_count minus 1:
                proc emit with ctx, ", "
            End If
            Set j to j plus 1
        End While
        proc emit with ctx, ")"
    End If

    Let body be proc hir_get_function_body from HIR with function_node
    If body is not equal to 0:
        proc emit with ctx, " "
        proc generate_statement with ctx, body
    Otherwise:
        proc emit with ctx, ";\n"
    End If
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emits the modifier-list tail of a function or modifier declaration: the
space-separated visibility (public/private/internal/external),
mutability (view/pure/payable), virtual, override, and user modifiers
(e.g. 'onlyOwner') in the HIR-supplied order. Solidity is lenient about
modifier ordering, so verbatim order is correct.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Collects the multi-valued 'solidity_modifier' metadata via
get_all_metadata_values. Emits each as ' TAG' (leading space). No
trailing punctuation - the caller controls termination.
@End Implementation
Process called "generate_modifier_tail" takes ctx as Integer, function_node as Integer:
    Let modifiers_meta be proc hir_get_metadata from HIR with function_node, "solidity_modifier"
    Let modifiers be proc get_all_metadata_values with modifiers_meta
    Let modifier_count be proc list_length from ListCore with modifiers
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than modifier_count:
        Let modifier be proc list_get from ListCore with modifiers, i
        proc emit with ctx, " "
        proc emit with ctx, modifier
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
End Process

@Reasoning:
Single-parameter emitter shared by function/modifier parameter lists.
Emits 'TYPE [STORAGE] [NAME]'.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads param name and Solidity type. Emits TYPE. Reads 'solidity_storage';
if non-empty appends ' STORAGE'. Emits ' NAME' if name is non-empty.
@End Implementation
Process called "generate_parameter" takes ctx as Integer, param_node as Integer:
    Let param_name be proc hir_get_parameter_name from HIR with param_node
    Let param_type be proc hir_get_metadata from HIR with param_node, "solidity_type"

    proc emit_type with ctx, param_type

    Let storage_loc be proc hir_get_metadata from HIR with param_node, "solidity_storage"
    Let storage_len be proc safe_string_length with storage_loc
    If storage_len is greater than 0:
        proc emit with ctx, " "
        proc emit with ctx, storage_loc
    End If

    Let param_name_len be proc safe_string_length with param_name
    If param_name_len is greater than 0:
        proc emit with ctx, " "
        proc emit with ctx, param_name
    End If
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: STATEMENT GENERATION
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Statement-level dispatcher driven entirely by hir_node_type. Each kind
short-circuits via Return after emitting. Block, if, while, for,
do-while, return, break, continue, try, and expression statements are
all handled; emit/revert/unchecked are recovered from metadata tags.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads hir_node_type and routes: HIR_BLOCK -> generate_block;
HIR_IF -> generate_if_statement; HIR_WHILE -> generate_while_statement;
HIR_FOR -> generate_for_statement; HIR_DO_WHILE ->
generate_do_while_statement; HIR_RETURN -> generate_return_statement;
HIR_BREAK -> 'break;'; HIR_CONTINUE -> 'continue;'; HIR_TRY ->
generate_try_statement; HIR_THROW -> generate_throw_statement;
HIR_EXPR_STMT -> generate_expression_statement.
@End Implementation
Process called "generate_statement" takes ctx as Integer, stmt_node as Integer:
    Let kind be proc hir_node_type from HIR with stmt_node

    If kind is equal to HIR.HIR_BLOCK:
        proc generate_block with ctx, stmt_node
        Return
    End If
    If kind is equal to HIR.HIR_IF:
        proc generate_if_statement with ctx, stmt_node
        Return
    End If
    If kind is equal to HIR.HIR_WHILE:
        proc generate_while_statement with ctx, stmt_node
        Return
    End If
    If kind is equal to HIR.HIR_FOR:
        proc generate_for_statement with ctx, stmt_node
        Return
    End If
    If kind is equal to HIR.HIR_DO_WHILE:
        proc generate_do_while_statement with ctx, stmt_node
        Return
    End If
    If kind is equal to HIR.HIR_RETURN:
        proc generate_return_statement with ctx, stmt_node
        Return
    End If
    If kind is equal to HIR.HIR_BREAK:
        proc emit_indent with ctx
        proc emit with ctx, "break;\n"
        Return
    End If
    If kind is equal to HIR.HIR_CONTINUE:
        proc emit_indent with ctx
        proc emit with ctx, "continue;\n"
        Return
    End If
    If kind is equal to HIR.HIR_TRY:
        proc generate_try_statement with ctx, stmt_node
        Return
    End If
    If kind is equal to HIR.HIR_THROW:
        proc generate_throw_statement with ctx, stmt_node
        Return
    End If
    If kind is equal to HIR.HIR_EXPR_STMT:
        proc generate_expression_statement with ctx, stmt_node
        Return
    End If
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emits a Solidity brace-delimited block. The opening brace lands on the
current cursor position (no fresh emit_indent) so 'if (...) {' attaches
the brace to the previous line. An 'unchecked' block (tagged
"solidity_unchecked") emits the 'unchecked' keyword before the brace.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
If the block is tagged solidity_unchecked emits 'unchecked '. Emits
'{\n'. increase_indent. Loops hir_get_block_statements recursing
generate_statement. decrease_indent. emit_indent + '}\n'.
@End Implementation
Process called "generate_block" takes ctx as Integer, block_node as Integer:
    Let is_unchecked be proc hir_get_metadata from HIR with block_node, "solidity_unchecked"
    Let unchecked_len be proc safe_string_length with is_unchecked
    If unchecked_len is greater than 0:
        proc emit with ctx, "unchecked "
    End If

    proc emit with ctx, "{\n"

    proc increase_indent with ctx

    Let statements be proc hir_get_block_statements from HIR with block_node
    Let stmt_count be 0
    If statements is not equal to 0:
        Set stmt_count to proc list_length from ListCore with statements
    End If
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than stmt_count:
        Let stmt be proc list_get from ListCore with statements, i
        proc generate_statement with ctx, stmt
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    proc decrease_indent with ctx
    proc emit_indent with ctx
    proc emit with ctx, "}\n"
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emits 'if (cond) thenStmt' with optional 'else elseStmt'. The branches
pass through generate_statement; the HIR is expected to wrap bodies in
block nodes.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
emit_indent + 'if (' + generate_expression(condition) + ') ' +
generate_statement(then). If else is non-null: emit_indent + 'else ' +
generate_statement(else).
@End Implementation
Process called "generate_if_statement" takes ctx as Integer, if_node as Integer:
    Let condition be proc hir_get_if_condition from HIR with if_node
    Let then_stmt be proc hir_get_if_then from HIR with if_node
    Let else_stmt be proc hir_get_if_else from HIR with if_node

    proc emit_indent with ctx
    proc emit with ctx, "if ("
    proc generate_expression with ctx, condition, 0
    proc emit with ctx, ") "

    proc generate_statement with ctx, then_stmt

    If else_stmt is not equal to 0:
        proc emit_indent with ctx
        proc emit with ctx, "else "
        proc generate_statement with ctx, else_stmt
    End If
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emits 'while (cond) body'.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
emit_indent + 'while (' + generate_expression(condition) + ') ' +
generate_statement(body).
@End Implementation
Process called "generate_while_statement" takes ctx as Integer, while_node as Integer:
    Let condition be proc hir_get_while_condition from HIR with while_node
    Let body be proc hir_get_while_body from HIR with while_node

    proc emit_indent with ctx
    proc emit with ctx, "while ("
    proc generate_expression with ctx, condition, 0
    proc emit with ctx, ") "

    proc generate_statement with ctx, body
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emits the C-style 'for (init; cond; update) body'. The init slot is a
statement (declaration or expression statement); its own trailing
semicolon/newline is suppressed by emitting the init inline. Condition
and update are expressions. Empty header slots emit nothing between the
separating semicolons.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
emit_indent + 'for ('. Emits the init via generate_for_init (inline, no
newline), then '; '. Emits the condition expression if present, then
'; '. Emits the update expression if present. Emits ') ' +
generate_statement(body).
@End Implementation
Process called "generate_for_statement" takes ctx as Integer, for_node as Integer:
    Let init be proc hir_get_for_init from HIR with for_node
    Let condition be proc hir_get_for_condition from HIR with for_node
    Let update be proc hir_get_for_update from HIR with for_node
    Let body be proc hir_get_for_body from HIR with for_node

    proc emit_indent with ctx
    proc emit with ctx, "for ("

    If init is not equal to 0:
        proc generate_for_init with ctx, init
    End If
    proc emit with ctx, "; "

    If condition is not equal to 0:
        proc generate_expression with ctx, condition, 0
    End If
    proc emit with ctx, "; "

    If update is not equal to 0:
        proc generate_expression with ctx, update, 0
    End If

    proc emit with ctx, ") "

    proc generate_statement with ctx, body
End Process

@Reasoning:
The for-loop init is a statement in HIR but must be emitted inline (no
indentation, no trailing ';\n') inside the for header. This helper
emits the bare expression of an expression-statement init, or for any
other statement kind, the underlying expression, without punctuation.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
If the init is a HIR_EXPR_STMT, emits its inner expression. Otherwise
treats the init as an expression and emits it directly. No semicolon or
newline is appended; the for header supplies the separators.
@End Implementation
Process called "generate_for_init" takes ctx as Integer, init_node as Integer:
    Let kind be proc hir_node_type from HIR with init_node
    If kind is equal to HIR.HIR_EXPR_STMT:
        Let inner be proc hir_get_expression_statement_expr from HIR with init_node
        proc generate_expression with ctx, inner, 0
        Return
    End If

    proc generate_expression with ctx, init_node, 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emits 'do body while (cond);'. The do-while keeps body-first semantics.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
emit_indent + 'do ' + generate_statement(body) + emit_indent + 'while ('
+ generate_expression(condition) + ');\n'.
@End Implementation
Process called "generate_do_while_statement" takes ctx as Integer, do_while_node as Integer:
    Let body be proc hir_get_do_while_body from HIR with do_while_node
    Let condition be proc hir_get_do_while_condition from HIR with do_while_node

    proc emit_indent with ctx
    proc emit with ctx, "do "
    proc generate_statement with ctx, body
    proc emit_indent with ctx
    proc emit with ctx, "while ("
    proc generate_expression with ctx, condition, 0
    proc emit with ctx, ");\n"
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emits 'return [expr];'. The value is optional.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
emit_indent + 'return'. If hir_get_return_value is non-null appends ' '
+ generate_expression(value). Terminates ';\n'.
@End Implementation
Process called "generate_return_statement" takes ctx as Integer, return_node as Integer:
    proc emit_indent with ctx
    proc emit with ctx, "return"

    Let value be proc hir_get_return_value from HIR with return_node
    If value is not equal to 0:
        proc emit with ctx, " "
        proc generate_expression with ctx, value, 0
    End If

    proc emit with ctx, ";\n"
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emits a Solidity `try EXPR { ... } catch ... { ... }` statement. The
try expression is preserved as "solidity_try_expr" metadata; the
success body is the try block; the catch clauses are the catch list.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
emit_indent + 'try ' + generate_expression(solidity_try_expr) + ' '.
generate_statement(try_block). Iterates hir_get_catch_clauses emitting
each via generate_catch_clause.
@End Implementation
Process called "generate_try_statement" takes ctx as Integer, try_node as Integer:
    proc emit_indent with ctx
    proc emit with ctx, "try "

    Let try_expr be proc hir_get_metadata from HIR with try_node, "solidity_try_expr"
    If try_expr is not equal to 0:
        proc generate_expression with ctx, try_expr, 0
        proc emit with ctx, " "
    End If

    Let try_block be proc hir_get_try_block from HIR with try_node
    proc generate_statement with ctx, try_block

    Let catches be proc hir_get_catch_clauses from HIR with try_node
    Let catch_count be 0
    If catches is not equal to 0:
        Set catch_count to proc list_length from ListCore with catches
    End If
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than catch_count:
        Let catch_clause be proc list_get from ListCore with catches, i
        proc generate_catch_clause with ctx, catch_clause
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emits 'catch (VAR) { body }' for one catch clause. The catch variable
defaults to a low-level catch when not named.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
emit_indent + 'catch '. If the catch variable is non-empty emits
'(VAR) '. Emits generate_statement(catch_body).
@End Implementation
Process called "generate_catch_clause" takes ctx as Integer, catch_node as Integer:
    proc emit_indent with ctx
    proc emit with ctx, "catch "

    Let catch_var be proc hir_get_catch_variable from HIR with catch_node
    Let var_len be proc safe_string_length with catch_var
    If var_len is greater than 0:
        proc emit with ctx, "("
        proc emit with ctx, catch_var
        proc emit with ctx, ") "
    End If

    Let body be proc hir_get_catch_body from HIR with catch_node
    proc generate_statement with ctx, body
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emits a Solidity `revert ...;` statement from a HIR throw tagged
"solidity_revert". The thrown expression is the error call/message; a
bare 'revert' identifier round-trips to plain 'revert();'.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
emit_indent + 'revert'. Reads the throw expression. If it is the bare
'revert' identifier, emits '()'. Otherwise emits ' ' + the expression.
Terminates ';\n'.
@End Implementation
Process called "generate_throw_statement" takes ctx as Integer, throw_node as Integer:
    proc emit_indent with ctx
    proc emit with ctx, "revert"

    Let expr be proc hir_get_throw_expression from HIR with throw_node
    Let expr_kind be proc hir_node_type from HIR with expr
    Let is_bare be 0
    If expr_kind is equal to HIR.HIR_IDENTIFIER:
        Let name be proc hir_get_identifier_name from HIR with expr
        Let is_revert be proc safe_string_equals with name, "revert"
        If is_revert is equal to 1:
            Set is_bare to 1
        End If
    End If

    If is_bare is equal to 1:
        proc emit with ctx, "()"
    Otherwise:
        proc emit with ctx, " "
        proc generate_expression with ctx, expr, 0
    End If

    proc emit with ctx, ";\n"
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emits an expression evaluated for its side effect: 'expr;'. An emit
statement (tagged "solidity_emit") prefixes the 'emit' keyword; an
assembly carrier (tagged "solidity_assembly") emits the raw assembly
block verbatim.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
emit_indent. If "solidity_assembly" is present, emits 'assembly ' +
the raw body and ';\n' is omitted (assembly blocks self-terminate with
their braces). If "solidity_emit" is present emits 'emit '. Then
generate_expression(inner) + ';\n'.
@End Implementation
Process called "generate_expression_statement" takes ctx as Integer, expr_stmt as Integer:
    Let assembly be proc hir_get_metadata from HIR with expr_stmt, "solidity_assembly"
    Let assembly_len be proc safe_string_length with assembly
    If assembly_len is greater than 0:
        proc emit_indent with ctx
        proc emit with ctx, "assembly "
        proc emit with ctx, assembly
        proc emit with ctx, "\n"
        Return
    End If

    proc emit_indent with ctx

    Let is_emit be proc hir_get_metadata from HIR with expr_stmt, "solidity_emit"
    Let emit_len be proc safe_string_length with is_emit
    If emit_len is greater than 0:
        proc emit with ctx, "emit "
    End If

    Let expr be proc hir_get_expression_statement_expr from HIR with expr_stmt
    proc generate_expression with ctx, expr, 0
    proc emit with ctx, ";\n"
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: EXPRESSION GENERATION
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Expression-level dispatcher driven by hir_node_type. The parent_prec
argument is the binding strength of the enclosing operator; binary
sub-expressions use it to decide parenthesisation. Literal kinds are
inlined here since each reduces to one emit pair. Number literals
(tagged "solidity_number") emit their exact lexeme unquoted; plain
string literals emit with quotes; booleans emit true/false.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
hir_node_type cascade: HIR_BINARY_EXPR -> generate_binary_expression;
HIR_UNARY_EXPR -> generate_unary_expression; HIR_ASSIGN_EXPR ->
generate_assign_expression; HIR_TERNARY_EXPR -> generate_ternary_expression;
HIR_CALL_EXPR -> generate_call_expression; HIR_NEW -> generate_new_expression;
HIR_MEMBER_EXPR -> generate_member_expression; HIR_INDEX_EXPR ->
generate_index_expression; HIR_LIST_LITERAL -> generate_array_literal;
HIR_STRING_LITERAL -> bare-or-quoted by "solidity_number"; HIR_INT_LITERAL
-> integer text; HIR_BOOL_LITERAL -> true/false; HIR_IDENTIFIER -> name.
@End Implementation
Process called "generate_expression" takes ctx as Integer, expr_node as Integer, parent_prec as Integer:
    If expr_node is equal to 0:
        Return
    End If

    Let kind be proc hir_node_type from HIR with expr_node

    If kind is equal to HIR.HIR_BINARY_EXPR:
        proc generate_binary_expression with ctx, expr_node, parent_prec
        Return
    End If
    If kind is equal to HIR.HIR_UNARY_EXPR:
        proc generate_unary_expression with ctx, expr_node
        Return
    End If
    If kind is equal to HIR.HIR_ASSIGN_EXPR:
        proc generate_assign_expression with ctx, expr_node
        Return
    End If
    If kind is equal to HIR.HIR_TERNARY_EXPR:
        proc generate_ternary_expression with ctx, expr_node
        Return
    End If
    If kind is equal to HIR.HIR_CALL_EXPR:
        proc generate_call_expression with ctx, expr_node
        Return
    End If
    If kind is equal to HIR.HIR_NEW:
        proc generate_new_expression with ctx, expr_node
        Return
    End If
    If kind is equal to HIR.HIR_MEMBER_EXPR:
        proc generate_member_expression with ctx, expr_node
        Return
    End If
    If kind is equal to HIR.HIR_INDEX_EXPR:
        proc generate_index_expression with ctx, expr_node
        Return
    End If
    If kind is equal to HIR.HIR_LIST_LITERAL:
        proc generate_array_literal with ctx, expr_node
        Return
    End If
    If kind is equal to HIR.HIR_STRING_LITERAL:
        Let is_number be proc hir_get_metadata from HIR with expr_node, "solidity_number"
        Let number_len be proc safe_string_length with is_number
        Let str_value be proc hir_get_string_literal_value from HIR with expr_node
        If number_len is greater than 0:
            proc emit with ctx, str_value
        Otherwise:
            proc emit with ctx, "\""
            proc emit with ctx, str_value
            proc emit with ctx, "\""
        End If
        Return
    End If
    If kind is equal to HIR.HIR_INT_LITERAL:
        Let int_value be proc hir_get_int_literal_value from HIR with expr_node
        proc emit_int with ctx, int_value
        Return
    End If
    If kind is equal to HIR.HIR_BOOL_LITERAL:
        Let bool_value be proc hir_get_bool_literal_value from HIR with expr_node
        If bool_value is equal to 1:
            proc emit with ctx, "true"
        Otherwise:
            proc emit with ctx, "false"
        End If
        Return
    End If
    If kind is equal to HIR.HIR_IDENTIFIER:
        Let name be proc hir_get_identifier_name from HIR with expr_node
        proc emit with ctx, name
        Return
    End If
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emits 'LEFT OP RIGHT' using the exact Solidity operator spelling from
"solidity_operator" metadata. The whole expression is wrapped in
parentheses when its precedence is strictly less than the enclosing
operator's precedence, and each operand is generated with this
operator's precedence as the parent so nested lower-precedence
sub-expressions parenthesise themselves. This guarantees the re-emitted
source re-parses to a structurally identical tree.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads the operator string (or maps the HIR opcode when metadata is
absent) and its precedence. Computes self_prec. If self_prec <
parent_prec, emits '(' ... ')'. Generates left with self_prec, ' OP ',
right with self_prec.
@End Implementation
Process called "generate_binary_expression" takes ctx as Integer, binary_node as Integer, parent_prec as Integer:
    Let operator be proc hir_get_metadata from HIR with binary_node, "solidity_operator"
    Let op_len be proc safe_string_length with operator
    If op_len is equal to 0:
        Let opcode be proc hir_get_binary_op from HIR with binary_node
        Set operator to proc opcode_to_solidity with opcode
    End If

    Let left be proc hir_get_binary_left from HIR with binary_node
    Let right be proc hir_get_binary_right from HIR with binary_node

    Let self_prec be proc solidity_operator_precedence with operator

    Let needs_paren be 0
    If self_prec is less than parent_prec:
        Set needs_paren to 1
    End If

    If needs_paren is equal to 1:
        proc emit with ctx, "("
    End If

    proc generate_expression with ctx, left, self_prec
    proc emit with ctx, " "
    proc emit with ctx, operator
    proc emit with ctx, " "
    proc generate_expression with ctx, right, self_prec

    If needs_paren is equal to 1:
        proc emit with ctx, ")"
    End If
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emits a Solidity unary form. Prefix operators ('!', '-', '~', '++',
'--', 'delete') are emitted before the operand; postfix '++'/'--'
after. The exact operator comes from "solidity_unary_operator"; the
"solidity_prefix" flag selects position. `delete` requires a trailing
space before its operand.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads operator and prefix flag. For prefix: emit operator (+ a space
for the 'delete' keyword) then the operand at unary precedence. For
postfix: emit the operand then the operator.
@End Implementation
Process called "generate_unary_expression" takes ctx as Integer, unary_node as Integer:
    Let operator be proc hir_get_metadata from HIR with unary_node, "solidity_unary_operator"
    Let op_len be proc safe_string_length with operator
    If op_len is equal to 0:
        Let opcode be proc hir_get_unary_op from HIR with unary_node
        Set operator to proc unary_opcode_to_solidity with opcode
    End If

    Let operand be proc hir_get_unary_operand from HIR with unary_node
    Let prefix_flag be proc hir_get_metadata from HIR with unary_node, "solidity_prefix"
    Let is_postfix be proc safe_string_equals with prefix_flag, "false"

    Let unary_prec be 13

    If is_postfix is equal to 1:
        proc generate_expression with ctx, operand, unary_prec
        proc emit with ctx, operator
    Otherwise:
        proc emit with ctx, operator
        Let is_delete be proc safe_string_equals with operator, "delete"
        If is_delete is equal to 1:
            proc emit with ctx, " "
        End If
        proc generate_expression with ctx, operand, unary_prec
    End If
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emits a Solidity assignment 'LHS OP RHS' (OP is '=' or a compound
operator like '+='). The whole assignment is the lowest-precedence
expression form, so it parenthesises itself when embedded in a tighter
context.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads lhs, the operator string, and rhs. Generates lhs, ' OP ', rhs.
Assignment uses precedence 1 (same as the lowest level) for its
operands so nested assignments and ternaries do not over-parenthesise.
@End Implementation
Process called "generate_assign_expression" takes ctx as Integer, assign_node as Integer:
    Let lhs be proc hir_get_assign_lhs from HIR with assign_node
    Let rhs be proc hir_get_assign_rhs from HIR with assign_node
    Let operator be proc hir_get_metadata from HIR with assign_node, "solidity_operator"
    Let op_len be proc safe_string_length with operator
    If op_len is equal to 0:
        Set operator to proc hir_get_assign_op from HIR with assign_node
    End If

    proc generate_expression with ctx, lhs, 1
    proc emit with ctx, " "
    proc emit with ctx, operator
    proc emit with ctx, " "
    proc generate_expression with ctx, rhs, 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emits 'cond ? then : else'. The ternary is the second-lowest precedence
form; its operands are generated at ternary precedence.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads condition/then/else and emits 'C ? T : E' with each operand at
ternary precedence (1).
@End Implementation
Process called "generate_ternary_expression" takes ctx as Integer, ternary_node as Integer:
    Let condition be proc hir_get_ternary_condition from HIR with ternary_node
    Let then_expr be proc hir_get_ternary_then from HIR with ternary_node
    Let else_expr be proc hir_get_ternary_else from HIR with ternary_node

    proc generate_expression with ctx, condition, 1
    proc emit with ctx, " ? "
    proc generate_expression with ctx, then_expr, 1
    proc emit with ctx, " : "
    proc generate_expression with ctx, else_expr, 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emits 'CALLEE(arg1, arg2, ...)'. The callee is a general expression, so
member calls and chained calls emit correctly through the recursive
path. A 'payable'/cast call (tagged solidity_payable/solidity_cast) is
just a regular call on the payable/type identifier.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Generates the callee at primary precedence. Emits '('. Iterates
hir_get_call_arguments generating each (at lowest precedence so commas
separate them) with ', ' between. Emits ')'.
@End Implementation
Process called "generate_call_expression" takes ctx as Integer, call_node as Integer:
    Let callee be proc hir_get_call_callee from HIR with call_node

    proc generate_expression with ctx, callee, 13
    proc emit with ctx, "("

    Let arguments be proc hir_get_call_arguments from HIR with call_node
    Let arg_count be 0
    If arguments is not equal to 0:
        Set arg_count to proc list_length from ListCore with arguments
    End If
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than arg_count:
        Let arg be proc list_get from ListCore with arguments, i
        proc generate_expression with ctx, arg, 1
        If i is less than arg_count minus 1:
            proc emit with ctx, ", "
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    proc emit with ctx, ")"
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emits 'new TYPE(args)'. The new operator allocates a new instance
(contract deployment) or array.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads the type name. Emits 'new TYPE('. Iterates hir_get_new_arguments
generating each with ', ' between. Emits ')'.
@End Implementation
Process called "generate_new_expression" takes ctx as Integer, new_node as Integer:
    Let type_name be proc hir_get_new_type_name from HIR with new_node

    proc emit with ctx, "new "
    proc emit with ctx, type_name
    proc emit with ctx, "("

    Let arguments be proc hir_get_new_arguments from HIR with new_node
    Let arg_count be 0
    If arguments is not equal to 0:
        Set arg_count to proc list_length from ListCore with arguments
    End If
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than arg_count:
        Let arg be proc list_get from ListCore with arguments, i
        proc generate_expression with ctx, arg, 1
        If i is less than arg_count minus 1:
            proc emit with ctx, ", "
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    proc emit with ctx, ")"
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emits 'OBJECT.MEMBER'. Solidity uses '.' for both contract-member and
struct-field access; the syntactic form is identical.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Generates the object at primary precedence. Emits '.'. Emits the member
name.
@End Implementation
Process called "generate_member_expression" takes ctx as Integer, member_node as Integer:
    Let object be proc hir_get_member_object from HIR with member_node
    Let member_name be proc hir_get_member_name from HIR with member_node

    proc generate_expression with ctx, object, 13
    proc emit with ctx, "."
    proc emit with ctx, member_name
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emits 'OBJECT[INDEX]'. Solidity uses [] for arrays and mappings.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Generates the object at primary precedence. Emits '['. Generates the
index at lowest precedence. Emits ']'.
@End Implementation
Process called "generate_index_expression" takes ctx as Integer, index_node as Integer:
    Let object be proc hir_get_index_object from HIR with index_node
    Let index be proc hir_get_index_value from HIR with index_node

    proc generate_expression with ctx, object, 13
    proc emit with ctx, "["
    proc generate_expression with ctx, index, 1
    proc emit with ctx, "]"
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emits an inline array literal '[e1, e2, ...]'.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Emits '['. Iterates hir_get_list_elements generating each at lowest
precedence with ', ' between. Emits ']'.
@End Implementation
Process called "generate_array_literal" takes ctx as Integer, array_node as Integer:
    proc emit with ctx, "["

    Let elements be proc hir_get_list_elements from HIR with array_node
    Let element_count be 0
    If elements is not equal to 0:
        Set element_count to proc list_length from ListCore with elements
    End If
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than element_count:
        Let element be proc list_get from ListCore with elements, i
        proc generate_expression with ctx, element, 1
        If i is less than element_count minus 1:
            proc emit with ctx, ", "
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    proc emit with ctx, "]"
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: OPERATOR PRECEDENCE AND OPCODE MAPPING
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Maps a Solidity binary-operator lexeme to its precedence level (low ->
high, 1..12 per the table in the file header). Used to decide
parenthesisation so the re-emitted expression re-parses to the same
tree. Comparison ladder over the operator strings.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
string_equals comparisons returning the integer precedence; unknown
operators get 2 (just above ternary) as a conservative default that
never strips required parentheses.
@End Implementation
Process called "solidity_operator_precedence" takes operator as Integer returns Integer:
    If proc safe_string_equals with operator, "||" is equal to 1:
        Return 2
    End If
    If proc safe_string_equals with operator, "&&" is equal to 1:
        Return 3
    End If
    If proc safe_string_equals with operator, "==" is equal to 1:
        Return 4
    End If
    If proc safe_string_equals with operator, "!=" is equal to 1:
        Return 4
    End If
    If proc safe_string_equals with operator, "<" is equal to 1:
        Return 5
    End If
    If proc safe_string_equals with operator, "<=" is equal to 1:
        Return 5
    End If
    If proc safe_string_equals with operator, ">" is equal to 1:
        Return 5
    End If
    If proc safe_string_equals with operator, ">=" is equal to 1:
        Return 5
    End If
    If proc safe_string_equals with operator, "|" is equal to 1:
        Return 6
    End If
    If proc safe_string_equals with operator, "^" is equal to 1:
        Return 7
    End If
    If proc safe_string_equals with operator, "&" is equal to 1:
        Return 8
    End If
    If proc safe_string_equals with operator, "<<" is equal to 1:
        Return 9
    End If
    If proc safe_string_equals with operator, ">>" is equal to 1:
        Return 9
    End If
    If proc safe_string_equals with operator, "+" is equal to 1:
        Return 10
    End If
    If proc safe_string_equals with operator, "-" is equal to 1:
        Return 10
    End If
    If proc safe_string_equals with operator, "*" is equal to 1:
        Return 11
    End If
    If proc safe_string_equals with operator, "/" is equal to 1:
        Return 11
    End If
    If proc safe_string_equals with operator, "%" is equal to 1:
        Return 11
    End If
    If proc safe_string_equals with operator, "**" is equal to 1:
        Return 12
    End If

    Return 2
End Process

@Reasoning:
Fallback operator-string recovery from an HIR opcode when the
"solidity_operator" metadata is absent (e.g. HIR built by a non-Solidity
producer feeding this backend). Returns the canonical Solidity spelling
for each HIR_OP_* binary code.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
If-ladder over the HIR_OP_* binary opcode constants returning the
matching Solidity operator string; defaults to '+'.
@End Implementation
Process called "opcode_to_solidity" takes opcode as Integer returns Integer:
    If opcode is equal to HIR.HIR_OP_ADD:
        Return "+"
    End If
    If opcode is equal to HIR.HIR_OP_SUBTRACT:
        Return "-"
    End If
    If opcode is equal to HIR.HIR_OP_MULTIPLY:
        Return "*"
    End If
    If opcode is equal to HIR.HIR_OP_DIVIDE:
        Return "/"
    End If
    If opcode is equal to HIR.HIR_OP_MODULO:
        Return "%"
    End If
    If opcode is equal to HIR.HIR_OP_EQUAL:
        Return "=="
    End If
    If opcode is equal to HIR.HIR_OP_NOT_EQUAL:
        Return "!="
    End If
    If opcode is equal to HIR.HIR_OP_LESS_THAN:
        Return "<"
    End If
    If opcode is equal to HIR.HIR_OP_LESS_EQUAL:
        Return "<="
    End If
    If opcode is equal to HIR.HIR_OP_GREATER_THAN:
        Return ">"
    End If
    If opcode is equal to HIR.HIR_OP_GREATER_EQUAL:
        Return ">="
    End If
    If opcode is equal to HIR.HIR_OP_LOGICAL_AND:
        Return "&&"
    End If
    If opcode is equal to HIR.HIR_OP_LOGICAL_OR:
        Return "||"
    End If
    If opcode is equal to HIR.HIR_OP_BITWISE_AND:
        Return "&"
    End If
    If opcode is equal to HIR.HIR_OP_BITWISE_OR:
        Return "|"
    End If
    If opcode is equal to HIR.HIR_OP_BITWISE_XOR:
        Return "^"
    End If
    If opcode is equal to HIR.HIR_OP_SHIFT_LEFT:
        Return "<<"
    End If
    If opcode is equal to HIR.HIR_OP_SHIFT_RIGHT:
        Return ">>"
    End If

    Return "+"
End Process

@Reasoning:
Fallback unary-operator recovery from an HIR opcode when the
"solidity_unary_operator" metadata is absent.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
If-ladder over the HIR_OP_* unary opcode constants returning the
matching Solidity unary spelling; defaults to '!'.
@End Implementation
Process called "unary_opcode_to_solidity" takes opcode as Integer returns Integer:
    If opcode is equal to HIR.HIR_OP_LOGICAL_NOT:
        Return "!"
    End If
    If opcode is equal to HIR.HIR_OP_NEGATE:
        Return "-"
    End If
    If opcode is equal to HIR.HIR_OP_BITWISE_NOT:
        Return "~"
    End If
    If opcode is equal to HIR.HIR_OP_INCREMENT:
        Return "++"
    End If
    If opcode is equal to HIR.HIR_OP_DECREMENT:
        Return "--"
    End If

    Return "!"
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: TYPE EXPRESSION GENERATION
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Emits a Solidity type reference held as a raw string ('uint256',
'address', 'mapping(address => uint256)', etc.). When the type is
absent (0 or empty) emits 'var' as a defensive placeholder so the
output stays syntactically shaped, though well-formed Solidity HIR
always supplies the type.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
If the type string is non-empty emits it; otherwise emits 'var'.
@End Implementation
Process called "emit_type" takes ctx as Integer, type_expr as Integer:
    Let type_len be proc safe_string_length with type_expr
    If type_len is greater than 0:
        proc emit with ctx, type_expr
    Otherwise:
        proc emit with ctx, "var"
    End If
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: METADATA UTILITIES
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
The multi-valued metadata keys this backend reads (solidity_modifier,
solidity_inherits, solidity_return) are written by the solidity_to_hir
frontend as a SINGLE ListCore handle per key (the HIR property
dictionary overwrites repeated keys, so the frontend accumulates all
values into one list and stores it once). This helper therefore just
normalises the stored value into a List the caller can iterate: the
list handle itself when present, or a fresh empty list when the key is
absent (0), so callers never null-check.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Returns a fresh empty list when meta is 0; otherwise returns meta
directly (it is the ListCore handle the frontend stored).
@End Implementation
Process called "get_all_metadata_values" takes meta as Integer returns Integer:
    If meta is equal to 0:
        Return proc list_create from ListCore
    End If
    Return meta
End Process

@Reasoning:
Resolves a callable node's parameter List in one step. hir_get_parameters
returns the callable as its own collection handle; hir_get_parameter_list
resolves that to the ordered List. Centralised so every member generator
reads parameters identically.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
hir_get_parameter_list(hir_get_parameters(node)).
@End Implementation
Process called "get_parameter_list" takes callable as Integer returns Integer:
    Let params be proc hir_get_parameters from HIR with callable
    Return proc hir_get_parameter_list from HIR with params
End Process

@Reasoning:
Null-safe string length. Metadata reads can legitimately return 0 for an
absent key; string_length on 0 is undefined, so this wrapper returns 0
length for a null handle.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Returns 0 when str is 0; otherwise string_length(str).
@End Implementation
Process called "safe_string_length" takes str as Integer returns Integer:
    If str is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc string_length from StringCore with str
End Process

@Reasoning:
Null-safe string equality. A metadata read of an absent key returns 0;
comparing 0 against a literal must yield "not equal" without faulting.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Returns 0 when a is 0; otherwise string_equals(a, b).
@End Implementation
Process called "safe_string_equals" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    If a is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc string_equals from StringCore with a, b
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: OUTPUT UTILITIES
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
The output primitive: appends a chunk of text to the context's running
output string. Every other generate_* routine flows through here.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
ctx.output := string_concat(ctx.output, text).
@End Implementation
Process called "emit" takes ctx as Integer, text as Integer:
    Set ctx.output to proc string_concat from StringUtils with ctx.output, text
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emits an integer value as its decimal text. Used for HIR_INT_LITERAL
nodes that carry a raw int64 payload (Solidity number literals usually
arrive as exact-lexeme string literals, but a core-built integer
literal feeding this backend is rendered here).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Converts the integer to a string via int_to_string and emits it.
@End Implementation
Process called "emit_int" takes ctx as Integer, value as Integer:
    Let text be proc integer_to_string from StringUtils with value
    proc emit with ctx, text
End Process

@Reasoning:
Writes four spaces per current indent level. Solidity's de-facto style
guide prescribes four-space indentation.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Loop 0..ctx.indent_level emitting a four-space string each iteration.
@End Implementation
Process called "emit_indent" takes ctx as Integer:
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than ctx.indent_level:
        proc emit with ctx, "    "
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
End Process

@Reasoning:
Bumps the indent counter so subsequent emit_indent calls produce one
more level. Paired with decrease_indent around any nested block.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
ctx.indent_level += 1.
@End Implementation
Process called "increase_indent" takes ctx as Integer:
    Set ctx.indent_level to ctx.indent_level plus 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Companion to increase_indent. Every increase has a paired decrease on
every exit path.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
ctx.indent_level -= 1.
@End Implementation
Process called "decrease_indent" takes ctx as Integer:
    Set ctx.indent_level to ctx.indent_level minus 1
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: PUBLIC API
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Public entry-point alias for generate_solidity_from_hir, providing the
'hir_to_<lang>' naming convention the translation pipeline drivers
expect when locating backends by symbol name.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Tail-calls generate_solidity_from_hir with the same hir_module argument.
@End Implementation
Process called "hir_to_solidity" takes hir_module as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc generate_solidity_from_hir with hir_module
End Process
